    "decisionConsequence": "Medium",
    "description": "FEA predicts construct stiffness, yield force, and force at 40 mm displacement for the non-cannulated 7.5 mm pedicle screw design under ASTM F1717 static compression-bending. Validated by direct comparison to bench testing (N=11 constructs across two laboratories). Model influence MEDIUM (testing confirms results); decision consequence MEDIUM (pedicle screw fracture leads to revision surgery, not death).",
    "deviceClass": "Class II",
    "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/cou/cou1-noncannulated",
    "intendedUse": "Demonstrate that the FEA modeling framework reproduces experimental compression-bending behavior of a non-cannulated pedicle screw construct within pre-established acceptance bounds (<10% QoI difference, E/uval < 1.96).",
    "modelInfluence": "Medium",
    "name": "COU1: Non-cannulated construct compression-bending prediction",
    "type": "ContextOfUse"
  },
  "hasValidationResult": [
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/result/stiffness-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Construct stiffness QoI comparison — FEA vs. experiment",
      "description": "FEA ensemble mean construct stiffness of 187.4 N/mm compared against experimental mean of 183.1 N/mm (N=11). Relative difference 2.3%, well within the 10% acceptance bound. E/uval = 0.41, below the 1.96 threshold. Validation activity executed by the FDA/Ansys/DePuy Synthes ensemble team under protocol NCA-VAL-001 Rev B; raw force-displacement curves archived in the bench-test datasets. All three FEA solvers agreed within 1.8% of each other, confirming solver independence for this QoI.",
      "prov:wasGeneratedBy": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/activity/val-run-stiffness-2023-09-14",
      "comparedAgainst": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/data/bench-test-lab1-n6"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/result/yield-force-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Yield force QoI comparison — FEA vs. experiment",
      "description": "FEA ensemble mean yield force of 1 342 N compared against experimental mean of 1 318 N (N=11). Relative difference 1.8%, within the 10% acceptance bound. E/uval = 0.53. Validation activity NCA-VAL-002 Rev A executed at Laboratory 2 under identical ASTM F1717 fixture conditions. Experimental uncertainty budget accounted for load-cell calibration (±0.5%), fixture alignment (±0.3%), and specimen-to-specimen geometric variability (±1.1%). The FEA model incorporated measured material coupon data (Ti-6Al-4V, n=8 coupons per lot) and as-built screw geometry from CMM measurements, providing high fidelity in the material and geometric inputs. Sensitivity analysis confirmed that yield force is primarily governed by screw root cross-section, which was replicated to within 0.05 mm in the FEA geometry. Inter-laboratory reproducibility was assessed by comparing Lab 1 and Lab 2 subsets; no statistically significant difference (p=0.31, two-sample t-test) was found, supporting pooling of the N=11 dataset. The combined experimental-numerical uncertainty metric E/uval remained below 1.96 for all three QoIs, satisfying the pre-specified acceptance criterion.",
      "comparedAgainst": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/data/bench-test-lab2-n5"
    },
    {
      "id": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/result/force-40mm-comparison",
      "type": "ValidationResult",
      "name": "Force at 40 mm displacement QoI comparison — FEA vs. experiment",
      "description": "FEA ensemble mean force at 40 mm displacement of 2 104 N compared against experimental mean of 2 089 N (N=11). Relative difference 0.7%, well within the 10% acceptance bound. E/uval = 0.29.",
      "prov:wasGeneratedBy": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/activity/val-run-force40mm-2023-09-14",
      "comparedAgainst": "https://uofa.net/nagaraja/data/bench-test-lab1-n6"
    }
